Modern society should be criticized for materialism as it is a detrament to our culture and our humanity.  => A

Part of this level of materialism includes, or is instigated by our reliance on technology. The two elements go hand in hand. At the same time, materialism isn't something new to our culture. Those with money have endulged in conspicious consumption for thousands of years. The only different now is our accessibility to material goods, again, through technology.

Our reliance on things and the ability to obtain them through technology have made our culture extremely shallow. People are constantly judged by what they own and wear and not who they are. We judge people on style and how they look. But once again, this is not a new concept. People have been judged on their physical appearance and the things they own since the Egyptians, if not earlier.
